-- Japanese Bought Net 386.3 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-01-12T23:57:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/japanese-bought-net-386-3-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Jan. 6 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 386.3 billion yen ($5.0 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 56.4 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 3.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 332.9 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 141.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 43.1 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1436.3 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1338
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
